This is a git repo setup on Linux


Create local repository
git init Mytest
cd Mytest


Create README and sample.c file
subl README
<created sample.c using File->New, File->Save As>


Add file to the Index. Index stores files/folders that are to be added into the Git repository.
git add README
git add sample.c


Once all the files have been added to the Index, we can commit them to the repository.
git commit -m "some_message"


Create new repository on GitHub via web interface,
…or create a new repository on the command line:
*** From GitHub ***
echo "# Mytest" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/mLangham/Mytest.git
git push -u origin main


Connect to GitHub repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/mLangham/Mytest.git


Push files from local repository into the remote host repository (GitHub)

git commit -m "initial commit"
git push origin master


*** From GitHub ***
…or push an existing repository from the command line

git remote add origin https://github.com/mLangham/Mytest.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main


